I believe the problem is that it is launching `/Applications/PowerShell.app/Contents/MacOS/PowerShell.sh` which `macOS` thinks requires `Rosetta`. I have testing by replacing this shell script with an `ARM64` compiled program solved this problem.

```
int main(int argc,char **argv)
{
	char *args[]={
		"/usr/bin/open",
		"/usr/local/bin/pwsh",
		NULL
	};

	execv(args[0],args);

	return 1;
}
```
